&lt;DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;Jewelcraft Skill of 299, No AA's, 15% mod (maxed trophy),&amp;nbsp;trivial 335&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;Expected Success Rate: 95%&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;1000 combines - 949&amp;nbsp; = 94.9% Success Rate&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;Jewelcraft Skill of 300, No AA's, 15% mod (maxed trophy),&amp;nbsp;trivial 335&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;Expected Success Rate: 95%&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;1000 combines - 960 = 96.0% Success Rate&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;It really looks like a perception thing and/or just bad luck for&amp;nbsp;people.&lt;/DIV&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;&lt;BR&gt;&#xD;
&lt;HR&gt;&#xD;
&lt;/BLOCKQUOTE&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;&lt;BR&gt;Nothing personal but when you run the same test with the idea you're going to improve your results and you don't get improved results, I think that is a problem. YOu are supposed to be luckier with the modifier not without it. Even though you want to argue statistics the fact is you got worse results with the torphies then without it all together. That said seems to me that there is a problem.&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;The high modifier skill level should automatically give you a better chance of success. I wonder if the fixed failure cap is actually messing with the statistical succes rate.&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;Although this should be the same basic equation for all of the trophies, all need to be tested.&lt;/P&gt;</description>
