      <title>Problem with success chance holding new trophies?</title>
      <link>http://eqforums.station.sony.com/eq/board/message?board.id=Trade&amp;message.id=11796#M11796</link>
      <description>&lt;div&gt;I am a tradeskill junkie, and really having fun with the new trophy quests.   Have completed 9 of them so far, at several different levels (3 - 6) and raised baking to 7.    As you know this requires a TON of subcombinations which you tend to make holding the appropriate trophy to maximize chance of success.    But seems to me that while holding the &amp;quot;new&amp;quot; tradeskill trophies my chance of success on a combination is LESS than when holding no trophy at all.    At first I thought this was just my imagination, but I went ahead and tested it using Jewelcraft skill.    My alt is 300 Jeweler with JCM 3 aa's.   Holding the new trophy (12% bonus) gives a triv of 336, and when making hundreds of combinations of &amp;quot;lacquered opal&amp;quot;  I noticed that I fail about 3 times more often than if I am NOT holding the new trophy (triv 300).    I understand there is some luck involved here, but I am talking about many hundreds of combinations each way, not just a few stacks...   Seems like luck would tend to average out with so many trials, statistically.   Also, attempted to cut 3 radiant augs holding the new trophy recently, and missed on all 3!    With my old trophy and JCM 3, success rate was generally 80 to 85% on this.    A miss of 3 out of 3 unimaginable.&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt; &lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;Just wondering, anyone else get this &amp;quot;wierd&amp;quot; feeling that the new trophies with higher mod trivs are&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;causing more failures that the old 5% trophies?    Perhaps there is some bug where aa's are not being accounted for properly?    Or, is it just my imagination?&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt; &lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;Coz&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt; &lt;/div&gt;</description>
